The students of Government Science College, Kagara, Niger State kidnapped by bandits have been freed, SaharaReporters has gathered.  Bandits, donning a military uniform, had around 2 am on Wednesday invaded the school and whisked away 27 pupils and 15 staff members after killing a Senior Secondary School 3 pupil. The incident has created nationwide agitation and worries over the kidnapped pupils' safety and school staff members, who were whisked away into the bush by the bandits.


 
